 LIBRARY DOCUMENTATION CENTRE.THE LIBRARY DOCUMENTATION CENTRE IS PART OF THE NATIONAL LIBRARY OF CANADAPUBLIC SERVICES BRANCH. IT WAS CREATED IN 1970 TO PROVIDE LITERATURE SUPPORTFOR THE WORK OF RESEARCH AND PLANNING BRANCH (NOW THE LIBRARY SYSTEMS CENTRE),TO MEET THE NEED FOR A CLEARINGHOUSE ON CANADIAN LIBRARY RESEARCH ANDDEVELOPMENT, AND TO SERVE LIBRARIES AND INDIVIDUALS (IN CANADA AND ABROAD)INTERESTED IN THIS SUBJECT. OUTLINES THE CENTRE'S COLLECTIONS, SERVICES, ANDPUBLICATIONS, AND STRESSES ITS HEAVY RELIANCE ON THE COOPERATION OF THECANADIAN LIBRARY COMMUNITY